    "bl_reason_item_wOqi5w": {
      "type": "bl-reason-item",
      "name": "BL - Reason Item",
      "settings": {
        "section_id": "",
        "bg_color": "#faf9f7",
        "number": "4",
        "title": "\"Is This Foundation Helping My Skin — Or Slowly Damaging It?\"",
        "body_text": "<p>This is the question almost nobody asks. And it might be the most important one of all. Because the foundation you wear for 10 to 14 hours a day, five to seven days a week, is either the best skincare product in your routine — or the worst.</p><p>Most foundations contain ingredients that actively work against mature skin. Denatured alcohol strips moisture. Heavy silicones prevent your skin from regulating itself. Synthetic fragrances — which can contain hundreds of undisclosed chemical compounds — trigger chronic low-grade inflammation that accelerates ageing. You're literally paying to make your skin worse while trying to make it look better.</p><p>A foundation designed properly for women over 40 should function as a leave-on treatment. Clinical-grade hydrating ingredients that increase moisture levels throughout the day. Antioxidants that neutralise free radical damage from UV and pollution. Niacinamide that strengthens your skin barrier and fades hyperpigmentation. Ask yourself: when I take this foundation off tonight, will my skin be better or worse than when I put it on this morning?</p>",
        "link_text": "",
